<div id="review_2318975765" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2318975765" />
    <a title="Eric" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11828590-eric"><img alt="Eric" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1452126300p2/11828590.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2318975765?book_show_action=true">Mar 19, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Eric" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Eric" href="/user/show/11828590-eric">Eric</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/8139058-heart-s-blood">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11828590-eric?shelf=2018-reading-challenge">2018-reading-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11828590-eric?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11828590-eric?shelf=folk-tales">folk-tales</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11828590-eric?shelf=kindle-read">kindle-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11828590-eric?shelf=romance">romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2318975765" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7951419660268969621">4.5 stars<br/><br/><i>Heart&apos;s Blood</i> is a surprisingly entertaining and satisfying fantasy read. I read this book as a buddy read with my friends in the Bookish Buddies book club. Another great choice!<br/><br/>When I embarked on reading this book, I had the impression that it was sort of retelling of the original <i>Beauty and the Beast</i>. I don&apos;t recall reading the original story. <i> Heart&apos;s Blood</i>, for me, bore very little resemblance to the more popular versions (ala Disney) of B&amp;B. There are no talking tea cups in this st</span>
  <span id="freeText7951419660268969621" style="display:none">4.5 stars<br /><br /><i>Heart's Blood</i> is a surprisingly entertaining and satisfying fantasy read. I read this book as a buddy read with my friends in the Bookish Buddies book club. Another great choice!<br /><br />When I embarked on reading this book, I had the impression that it was sort of retelling of the original <i>Beauty and the Beast</i>. I don't recall reading the original story. <i> Heart's Blood</i>, for me, bore very little resemblance to the more popular versions (ala Disney) of B&amp;B. There are no talking tea cups in this story. <br /><br />The story starts with Caitrin running away from her home town. She's a young woman who happens to be a professional scribe. A respectable craft that she learned from her father who had died suddenly. Caitrin finds herself in a weird land where there are "voices" in the forest full of ghosts. It so happens there is a scribe's job at the chieftain's manor. Caitrin is broke so decides she is going to inquire about the job. To get to the manor though, she has to travel through the haunted forest. She manages to get through the forest to meet the main caretaker, the kindly Mangus. She also meets the chieftain Anluan. Anluan, it turns out, to be a young man who has a disability. The are other strange people about the manor as well. Caitrin gets the job even though the people don't expect her to stay long. No one ever does.<br /><br />The writing has a fluidity to it that kept me hooked into the story. The characters are well developed and there are a lot of interesting story elements. The storytelling has a traditional feel and indeed a good part of the story is about hope, love, loyalty, good, evil and life lessons. I liked that story gets down to the person level of the characters. Also, sort of neatly tucked into the plot is a mystery and the search for clues. Parts of the story has horror elements to it while other parts are quite heartwarming. Finally, this story is written for adults and perhaps older teens.<br /><br />This story surprised me as being good fantasy with kind of traditional fairy tale feel. The author calls it "historical fantasy." Whatever the story style is called, it worked for me. I'll plan to explore more works by this author.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7951419660268969621" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


