<div id="review_2374431549" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2374431549" />
    <a title="Dyanna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30899684-dyanna"><img alt="Dyanna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1492086501p2/30899684.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2374431549?book_show_action=true">Oct 21, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dyanna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dyanna" href="/user/show/30899684-dyanna">Dyanna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781405039437" href="/book/show/7177275-heart-s-blood">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30899684-dyanna?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2374431549" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15670707383362100377">This book made me fall in love all over again with <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/8649.Juliet_Marillier' title='Juliet Marillier' rel='nofollow noopener'>Juliet Marillier</a>&apos;s books after I DNF ed <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13923.Blade_of_Fortriu__The_Bridei_Chronicles___2_' title='Blade of Fortriu (The Bridei Chronicles, #2) by Juliet Marillier' rel='nofollow noopener'>Blade of Fortriu</a>. This book is a retelling of the beloved fairy tale: <b>
  <i>Beauty and the Beast</i>
</b> and it is a good one !<br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1603372691ra/30272514.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/>This story follows Caitrin, a young woman that runs from her past and accepts the job of a scribe that is needed at Whistling Tor only to find herself in a haunted fortress were the chieftain is a crooked man that does not make a good impression to Caitrin the first time they met.<br/><br/>The story i</span>
  <span id="freeText15670707383362100377" style="display:none">This book made me fall in love all over again with <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/8649.Juliet_Marillier" title="Juliet Marillier" rel="nofollow noopener">Juliet Marillier</a>'s books after I DNF ed <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13923.Blade_of_Fortriu__The_Bridei_Chronicles___2_" title="Blade of Fortriu (The Bridei Chronicles, #2) by Juliet Marillier" rel="nofollow noopener">Blade of Fortriu</a>. This book is a retelling of the beloved fairy tale: <b>
  <i>Beauty and the Beast</i>
</b> and it is a good one !<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1603372691ra/30272514.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>This story follows Caitrin, a young woman that runs from her past and accepts the job of a scribe that is needed at Whistling Tor only to find herself in a haunted fortress were the chieftain is a crooked man that does not make a good impression to Caitrin the first time they met.<br><br>The story is about friendship, secrets, love, hope and the courage to confront the inner fears.<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1603372691ra/30272515.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>The atmosphere is creepy, the all entourage will grow to you and the romance was perfect and sweet so if you are a fan of Beauty and The Beast go for it!</span>
  <a data-text-id="15670707383362100377" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
