<div id="review_1959754321" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1959754321" />
    <a title="Lata" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13126933-lata"><img alt="Lata" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1525485137p2/13126933.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1959754321?book_show_action=true">Nov 05, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lata" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lata" href="/user/show/13126933-lata">Lata</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780451462930" href="/book/show/6391467-heart-s-blood">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13126933-lata?shelf=scifi-fantasy">scifi-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13126933-lata?shelf=x2017-read">x2017-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13126933-lata?shelf=auth-f">auth-f</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1959754321" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12934976414194875294">A sad-happy end to a lovely story about a wonderful young woman, Caitrin and the haunted, lonely cursed place she at first escapes to then makes as her home. Juliet Marillier has written beautifully and sensitively of a variety of characters, and of hope. Hope suffuses this narrative, and that and kindness are Caitrin as she struggles to help the chieftain of Whistling Tor and all the unusual inhabitants.<br/>I love the characterizations and the tone and language. Beautiful stuff!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


